title: For Sale:  Saiga 7.62x51 (.308) Carbine
location: Youngsville, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
For sale is a practically new Saiga .308 Carbine w/ 16" barrel. Only fired when tested at the factory and twice by me. Included are all original accessories: cleaning rod and cleaning kit, oil bottle, and manual. Also, will include 100 rounds of FMJ ammo.

If you aren't familiar with Saiga rifles, then I highly recommend that you do some reading and know exactly what you are buying. This is a true soviet-made kalashnikov pattern rifle. There are a lot of A.K. clones out there. Many of them are re-built from de-milled romanian receivers and stripped down junked parts kits, and aren't worth the time and effort it took to give them hardware and make them look shiny and new again, only to cut a big slice out of someone's wallet that doesn't know the difference. Don't be "that guy." Do your homework.

If you want to build a mega bad-ass A.K., a Saiga is a great place to start. This is an awesome project rifle, and the .308 is the easiest full conversion of all receivers. 

This is a stamped receiver, not milled. You should know the difference. The finish on them is little more than a high-temp flat black. It wears relatively easily, but is easy to re-finish or touch up. It isn't made to be pretty, it's a freakin "tractor." Can you drive a tank over a stamped receiver? Probably not. Is it still the same 110% reliable A.K. action? Abso-freakin-loutely! Drag it through the mud, pour some sand in it, throw it in the pond...it doesn't care. It will fire every time. It's an A.K.! Another big plus is these rifles can chew through the cheap soviet-made steel cased ammo like nobody's business! A very affordable rifle to shoot! 

You need to be familiar with 922R before you purchase this rifle. In it's stock configuration this rifle does not have enough U.S. parts to be legally used with high capacity magazines. Even a U.S. made magazine does not count as enough legal parts on it's own! KNOW 922R BEFORE YOU BUY THIS WEAPON!

The price is $450 FIRM. At this price you have saved an FFL transfer fee, shipping, tax, and are practically getting the ammo for free, so the price doesn't move. Not happening.

 You will get a much faster response by calling and LEAVING A MESSAGE. I will not return calls that do not leave a message. REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Walther P99 AS
postcontent:
Walther P99 AS ANTI STRESS 9MM Trigger Mechanism: Traditional Double Action with an Anti-Stress Mode As the first pistol equipped with a firing pin lock, the P99 AS combines the advantages of the traditional Double Action System with Single Action Anti-Stress trigger. The P99 provides the shooter with a user-friendliness previously found only in hammer fired pistols. Traditional Double Action The anti-stress trigger makes the P99 one of the world's safest firearms by preventing unintentional "reflex" firing in stressful situations. The decisive innovation: When the slide is racked completely to the rear upon loading, the trigger remains in the forward position for the first shot; not only in the double action trigger mode, but also in the single action mode. The trigger travel is .551" long in the anti-stress mode (at 4.4 lbs. trigger force), preventing inadvertent firing. On all subsequent shots, the trigger travel is reduced to .314" (at the same trigger force) and this permits firing in rapid sequence, due to the quick reset of the P99 trigger. Enhanced Safety The P99 AS is equipped with a decocking button to safely decock the striker. It acts as an automatic safety and is integrated directly into the slide to prevent snagging on clothing even if the gun is drawn quickly.
I personally have only put 75 rounds through it. I purchased it in December 2010. I do ask that we transfer it through an FFL. If you have any questions, please ask!
